snippet.textDisplay:
Everybody is enamored with the idea of a fighting, cowboy-esque president when they forgot one very important thing: in every cowboy movies the good guys never go for the gun immediately.

They would try to reason with the baddies, try to see their position, and more than one occasion would try to talk down the bad guys from doing something they might regret. It was always "Okay Cletus, you had your fun. Now why don't you let Widow Annie go and just turn around?" before their irreconcilable differences finally lead to a gunfight.

What Trump did was basically shooting Cletus before he even got his bad guy monologue, dropping the gun, raising his tiny baby hands ala Rocky and go, "I win! I killed Cletus! I am the good guy!" and even in the most cliched Hollywood narratives that action cannot be justified.
